{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"body":"## Plan-review + security-review status (handoff)\n\n**Design provenance:** brainstorm design-of-record is session log `emanatory-confounded-dodo`; the full journey (investigation, decisions, 3-reviewer security panel, and the round-by-round plan-review remediation) is captured in a follow-up session log recorded at handoff.\n\n**Plan-review status (source of truth = `rebar verify-signature <id> --kind plan-review`; NOTE: `--output json` stdout was frequently lost to empty files during this session — the signed attestation on the ticket, not the console JSON, is authoritative):**\n- Epic + S1 (holy-heartfelt-pheasant) + S2 (emersed-prettying-eagle) + S3 (lost-nonproift-stilt) + S4 (turbid-isogonal-iguana) + S5 (trogonoid-browny-blowfish) + S6 (witching-subjective-skylark): **PASS + signed** at last review.\n- S7 (fixed-jockeyish-swan): **plan review NOT yet run** — its description is authored (incl. the accepted port-configurability note); run `rebar review-plan fixed-jockeyish-swan` before claiming it.\n\n**Higher-effort security-review pass folded in.** A 3-reviewer adversarial panel (coherence + peer-alignment + red-team security) ran over the whole graph and produced a consolidated redesign now reflected in the descriptions. Load-bearing security decisions the implementer MUST preserve:\n- The **composite `TokenVerifier` is the single audience/fail-closed choke point** — the SDK's `BearerAuthBackend` never inspects `.resource` (grounded vs mcp 1.28.1), so the composite re-validates every returned token's `resource == auth_resource_server_url` (RFC 8707). No verifier (incl. custom) can bypass it.\n- **One resource, one audience:** a single `auth_resource_server_url`; per-verifier `audience` params were DROPPED to close a real hole.\n- Fail-closed everywhere (raise = non-acceptance, never acceptance); unknown strategy / empty composite / no-verifier-over-HTTP / unauth-HTTP-without-ack all refuse to start.\n- Transport hardening: DNS-rebinding/Origin on by default w/ explicit loopback defaults; non-loopback requires allowlists + TLS-at-edge ack; discovery URLs derive from configured `auth_resource_server_url` (behind-proxy fix), not the request scheme.\n\n**Cross-ticket / infra notes:**\n- **Orthogonal to epic `2141-0ba0-5313-48d4` (audit-trail UI).** That is a FastAPI browser dashboard (`src/rebar/audit/server.py`, `[reviewbot]` extra) — a DIFFERENT stack (FastAPI vs mcp SDK), protocol (HTML vs MCP JSON-RPC), audience (human vs agent), files, and config. No dependency edge or shared abstraction is warranted (would be premature coupling). Only incidental overlap: both land on Starlette+uvicorn, and both default to loopback `:8000` — S1's `http_port` is configurable to avoid the clash (noted in S7 docs). If de-dup is ever wanted, the target is the 3 FastAPI apps (review_bot, opcert_service, audit UI), NOT the mcp SDK transport.\n- **SDK API confirmed vs mcp v1.28.1:** `TokenVerifier`/`AccessToken(...,resource,...)`/`AuthSettings(issuer_url singular, no authorization_servers field)`/`TransportSecuritySettings`/`streamable_http_app()` all real; SDK's `IntrospectionTokenVerifier` is EXAMPLE-only (S4 writes its own). Pin `mcp>=1.28.1,<2` (S1 owns it, in BOTH the `mcp` and `[dev]` extras).\n- **Doc generators need fixing (S1 owns):** `scripts/gen_mcp_reference.py` hardcodes the gate-var tuple → must iterate `MCP_ENV_VARS`; `scripts/gen_env_registry.py` AST-scans literal `os.environ` → must ingest `MCP_ENV_VARS`. S7 regenerates docs for the full key set.\n- **Config is FLAT:** `_config_schema.py`'s `coerce_sparse` handles only one-level scalar keys (no nested `[mcp.auth]`, no list-of-tables). All auth config is flat `mcp.auth_*` scalars; the static-token records live in a verifier-parsed secrets file. TOML key `auth_x` ≠ env var name `REBAR_MCP_AUTH_X` (register the ENV-VAR names in `MCP_ENV_VARS`/`server.json`)."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1784090712541871001,"uuid":"3768ae2d-1fea-43fe-a0c6-29d4ed03ae66"}